name: Fibotsuke Postage Stamp
description: Fibotsuke city - 1881 (D.C) - was know for worshiping nature and using it as mesure, mentor and model. As a homage to this relationship with nature, a stamp was creted, mixing two of the most important elements for Fibostuke, nature and human culture.   This is the second stamp of a series of a digital postage stamp collection. Designed to acompany your Tezo's transactions and for digital postage stamp collection. Art created with fibonnaci curved vector modules. As a good practice, following Tezo's energy saving system design , 30% of the profit will be invested in nature-friendly/human-centered energy inciatives/technologies. Having this stamp means that at least you tried to save the world while buying cryptoart.
